viewRepresentation.text:
Guide

Required Tasks

This workflow can help you in labeling unlabeled documents using active learning.

The available data is about moview review. Please follow the instructions to upload your own unlabeled documents.

  • Upload your document in a CSV file with the exact columns showed in this example of movie reviews:

    • Title Text
    A great movie! I really enjoyed this movie because..
    Worst movie ever! I could not finish the movie because..
    ... ...

  • Double click the cells of the table to type in the classes labels. Add also abbreviations so that they are easy to type in afterwards. If you decide to upload a CSV file for your labels and abbreviations, your custom settings in the table will be ignored.

viewRepresentation.label: Upload Documents to be Labeled
viewRepresentation.description: Upload data as CSV file. It must contain a column named 'Title' and a column name 'Text'.

viewRepresentation.label: Upload Labels to be Used
viewRepresentation.description: Upload labels as CSV file. It must contain a column named 'Class Name' and a column name 'Class Abbreviation'.
